# 4. Find Intersection of Three Lists

## Problem

Find common elements present in all three lists.

### Example

```python
list1 = [1, 2, 3, 4]
list2 = [2, 3, 5]
list3 = [2, 3, 6]
```

### Output

```python
[2, 3]
```

## Built-in Solution

```python
list1 = [1, 2, 3, 4]
list2 = [2, 3, 5]
list3 = [2, 3, 6]

result = list(set(list1) & set(list2) & set(list3))

print(result)
```

## Pure Logic Solution

```python
list1 = [1, 2, 3, 4]
list2 = [2, 3, 5]
list3 = [2, 3, 6]

result = []

for num in list1:
    if num in list2 and num in list3:
        result.append(num)

print(result)
```

